        <h2><a href="http://www.thelmagazine.com/newyork/badminton-at-the-park/Event?oid=2201813">Badminton at the Park</a></h2>
        
        <p class="storyBody">
          Free badminton at the Open House Gallery's indoor park.
          
           
        </p>
        
        
        
          <p class="locationInfo">
            Open House Gallery, 201 Mulberry St., Nolita
          </p>
        
        </div>
        
          <div class="GoTBody" style="display:none">
        
        
        
        
        
        
        <h2><a href="http://www.thelmagazine.com/newyork/coolny-2012/Event?oid=2203730">CoolNY 2012</a></h2>
        
        <p class="storyBody">
          The cold weather counterpart to September's DUMBO Dance Festival, CoolNY is likewise free and full to bursting, with nearly 300 dancers and choreographers taking the Jay Street stage during the two-week festival. Among the emerging, established, local and international participants are resident troupe White Wave Young Soon Kim Dance Company and the Renegade Performance Group.
          
          FREE 
        </p>
        
        
        
          <p class="locationInfo">
            John Ryan Theater, 25 Jay St., at John St, Dumbo
          </p>
        
        </div>
        
          <div class="GoTBody" style="display:none">
        
        
        
        
        
                
          <div class="GoTimg">
            <a href="http://www.thelmagazine.com/events/mary-poppins/Event?oid=1146336">
              <img src="/imager/b/eventfeature/1146336/abe8/TUES_MaryPoppins_theater.jpg" width="450" height="300" alt="Mary Poppins" title="Mary Poppins" class="storyImg" />
            </a>
          </div>
        
        
        <h2><a href="http://www.thelmagazine.com/events/mary-poppins/Event?oid=1146336">Mary Poppins</a></h2>
        
        <p class="storyBody">
          Disney hopes to create another <i>Lion King</i>-type monster hit with this musical based on the beloved 1964 movie of the same name.
          
          $20-$110 
        </p>
        
        
        
          <p class="locationInfo">
            New Amsterdam Theater, 214 W 42nd St., between Broadway and Eighth Ave, Midtown East
          </p>
        
        </div>
      
